# TITLE         :CLM_BTEQ_EDW_CLM_LOAD 
# Filename      :CLM_BTEQ_EDW_CLM_LOAD.sh
# Description   :This Script is to load the EDW Table CLM from CLM_STG Staging Table and populate 
#                AUDIT STATISTICS table for CSA ROWCOUNT. This Script also inserts data into CLM_MAX_RVSN Table.
# SOURCE Tables :CLM_STG 
# TARGET Tables :CLM,CLM_MAX_RVSN
# KEY COLUMNS   :CLM_ADJSTMNT_KEY
# Developer     :COGNIZANT 
# Created ON    :07/10/2009 
# Location      :KOLKATA 
# Logic         :A) Pick up the latest records from CLM_STG Table and look up on RDM (CD_VAL_TRNSLTN)
#                to get the standardized code values, Then populate the records with standardized code values
#                into Global Temporary Table (WORK_CLM) used for temporary storing of data.based on the latest TRNSCTN_DTM.
#                Then records will be inserted into the CLM Table from Global Temporary Table (WORK_CLM)
#
#                B) The latest records are picked up on same  CLAIM SYSTEM OF RECORD CODE, MEMBER KEY and CLAIM NUMBER,
#                having MAXIMUM ADJUDICATION DATE , MAXIMUM ADJUSTMENT NUMBER and MAXIMUM IMAGE CODE from WORK_CLM Table
#                The records are populated in a Global Temporary Table WORK_CLM_MAX_RVSN.
#                Once the records are built,using same SOURCE SYSTEM CODE, MEMBER KEY and CLAIM NUMBER WITH
#                MAXIMUM ADJUDICATION DATE, MAXIMUM ADJUSTMENT NUMBER and MAXIMUM IMAGE CODE,
#                WORK_CLM_MAX_RVSN Table is searched to get the record.
#
#                I) When only one record is returned from the search and it is NOT A REVERSAL RECORD (CLM_DISP_CD<>'RVRSL')
#                that record is selected and populated into the CLM_MAX_RVSN Table. The previous entry for the same  
#                CLAIM SYSTEM OF RECORD CODE, MEMBER KEY and CLAIM NUMBER combination is deleted from CLM_MAX_RVSN.
#
#                II) When only one record is returned from the search and it is  A REVERSAL RECORD (CLM_DISP_CD='RVRSL')
#                that record is  not inserted into the CLM_MAX_RVSN Table. The previous entry for the same
#                CLAIM SYSTEM OF RECORD CODE, MEMBER KEY and CLAIM NUMBER combination is deleted from CLM_MAX_RVSN.
#                        
#                III) When more than one record is returned from the search and none of the records is reversal record 
#                (CLM_DISP_CD<>'RVRSL' FOR ALL), The first record sorted on ROW_NUMBER FUNCTION is selected and inserted
#                into the CLM_MAX_RVSN Table and rest of the records are populated in ERR_CLM_MAX_RVSN Table. The previos  
#                entry for same  CLAIM SYSTEM OF RECORD CODE, MEMBER KEY and CLAIM NUMBER combination is deleted from CLM_MAX_RVSN.
#
#                IV) When more than one record is returned from the search and any one of the records have CLM_DISP_CD=.'RVRSL'
#                result records are sorted on ROW_NUMBER FUNCTION and all the records are populated in ERR_CLM_MAX_RVSN Table
#                except the first one.The previos entry for same  CLAIM SYSTEM OF RECORD CODE, MEMBER KEY and CLAIM NUMBER 
#                combination is deleted from CLM_MAX_RVSN.
#                
#                Insert the records into the ERR_LOG Table Global Temporary Table (WORK_CLM) for which no RDM codes found in  
#                RDM Table. 
#                Load the count of WORK_CLM Table into AUDT_STTSTC Table for CSA ROWCOUNT
